						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone set up near the Kēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>13th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription commemorates the death of Mēdara Pāṁḍya near Bisilahaḷḷi when the teacher Mūṟujāvidēva was proceeding to Huligeṟe. The children of the deceased were compensated with a gift of land.</p>						

						<p>In characters of about 13th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
